Xi Jinping Sends Congratulatory Letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum - Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, December 11th. On December 11th, President Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum. Xi Jinping pointed out that the world is undergoing major changes unseen in a century, and global scientific and technological innovation has entered a period of intensive activity. The new round of technological revolution and industrial transformation has had a profound impact on the global economic structure. The Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area should focus on building an international science and technology innovation center and strive to build a global highland for science and technology innovation, promoting the development of emerging industries. China is willing to work with scientists from all countries and international science and technology organizations to strengthen international scientific and technological exchanges and cooperation, intensify research on major scientific issues, promote the breakthrough of common scientific and technological challenges, deepen collaboration on key scientific projects, jointly advance the development of world science, and better benefit humanity. The 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum opened on the same day in Guangzhou, Guangdong Province, with the theme "Exploring the Future, Sharing Science," and was hosted by the People's Government of Guangdong Province.
